    "behind_the_scenes": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What a Tuesday looks like",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>By 8 AM, three people are at the warehouse pulling the next month's items. Tools from a local supplier in Greensboro. Apparel printed by a friend in Asheville. Detailing supplies from a chemist in California who races on weekends.</p><p>Everything gets unboxed, inspected, photographed, and packed. Quality control flags anything that doesn't pass — wrong stitching, sketchy chrome, off-color print. Those go back. The rest goes in your box.</p><p>Boxes ship the 15th. Then we do it all again.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
